"3:179:23" : {s: 3, a: 179, w: 23, r: "جبي", t: "يَجْتَبِى", l: "ٱجْتَبَىٰ", lc: 10, tl: "yajtabī", lb: "মনোনীত করা",e: "chooses", b: "তিনি বেছে নেন", i: "Dia memilih", f: 2, rm: "He collected (e.g. water/tax). A mode/manner of collecting. He chose it/selected it for himself. He returned/receded/retreated/went back. Collecting in a way of choice/selection (i.e. God blessing Solomon more than others etc.) He forged/produced/invented it. Water collected. A watering trough in which water is collected. The place where a well is dug. What is around a well/watering trough. Dug wells in which shoots of grape-vines are set. A collector of water for camels. Locust (it collects everything by eating it), A company of men."},
